title: Trump Speaks After US Supreme Court Strikes Down Global Tariffs In 6-3 Ruling | 10 News
description: The US Supreme Court has struck down Donald Trump’s global tariffs in a 6-3 ruling, finding he had no authority under emergency powers to impose them.  A furious Trump labelled the justices “fools and lapdogs” and vowed to resurrect the policy, announcing plans for a new 10 per cent global tariff under separate trade laws.  The decision could force the US government to refund billions of dollars to businesses, including Australian exporters hit by the baseline 10 per cent tariff.  While country-specific tariffs are invalid, product-specific levies on goods such as steel, aluminium and cars remain in place.
